    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-02T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-02T04:00:00-05:00" n="845"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d845">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">346B.115 Standard Oil Co./15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-02T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 2, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 2—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1054. Department’s telegram No. 512, October 26, 4 p.m. Note and oral protest
                    delivered this morning to Anfuso, Chief of Cabinet at the Foreign Office. He did
                    not comment other than to say that while the incidents were regrettable they
                    occurred in the course of military operations. He said he would refer both
                    protests immediately to the Ministry of Italian Africa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
